== Markup source code

In Creole markup you can easy insert sourcecode: Use **{{{<<code ext=".EXT">>...<</code>>}}}** and PyLucid used Pygments to highlight it. Where '.EXT' is the typical fileextension/alias of the code, please look at:

 * http://pygments.org/docs/lexers/

=== examples

{{{
<<code ext=".css">>
/* CSS Stylesheet */
.xs {font-family:verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: x-small}
.m {font-size: medium}
<</code>>
}}}

result:

<<code ext=".css">>
/* CSS Stylesheet */
.xs {font-family:verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;font-size: x-small}
.m {font-size: medium}
<</code>>

Here a "error" example:

<<code ext=NotExists>>
If there exist no Lexer for the given format, PyLucid used the Pygments TextLexer. =;-)
<</code>>
The other way is to use Creole **<<html>>&#x7B;&#x7B;&#x7B;...&#x7D;&#x7D;&#x7D;<</html>>** code block tags.

